videos.title: Baby Truck Storm Rescue | Gecko's Garage | Cartoons For Kids | Toddler Fun Learning
videos.description:
A storm is brewing as Gecko fixes Mummy Truck's flat tyre by the side of the road after the wind blew a fence into the road and gave her a puncture while she was out with Baby Truck... once the job is done Gecko puts the fence posts into the back of Tilly to save another vehicle from the same fate. Suddenly a flash of lightning startles poor Baby Truck who drives into the trees for cover... Gecko and Mummy follow but are unable to find her and the storm is getting worse, so Gecko presses the emergency button in Tilly to alert Kat who soon arrives on scene. Using the radio in Tilly they communicate as Kat uses her aerial advantage and expert tracking skills to pick up Baby Truck's trail... sure enough they find her but she's become trapped on a piece of land surrounded by rising flood water! Kat does her best to grab Baby with the winch but the storm is raging and Baby is moving around frantically watching her dummy floating in the water having lost it in the panic. Thinking quickly, Gecko gets Tilly to tow him from the bank as he uses the fence posts as water skis to pick up Baby's dummy and then reach her. With Baby calmed Kat is able to grab on to her with the winch from Helena and lift Baby and Gecko to safety - hurrah!

Gecko’s Garage is an animated entertainment series for children aged between 2 and 5 set in a colorful world that’s jam-packed with friendly vehicles, helper robots and a mechanic called Gecko.

Baby comes into the garage with a wobbly tooth, confused about it. Gecko explains to her that's it's perfectly normal - when teeth fall out, you put them under your pillow and get a coin. It'll fall out naturally, it could happen at any moment. As Gecko says this however, Baby Truck sneezes (since Red is doing some spring cleaning with a feather duster) and the tooth flies out. Baby is worried - if she can't find her tooth, how will she get her coin? Gecko and the Mechs search the garage for the tooth, and after searching in some very odd places, they have to admit defeat. That is, until they notice the tooth got stuck in Red's feather duster - it's been there all along! Red hands it back to Baby, who is very grateful!
